a-spec.md               # AR-014: Valkey store delta spec\n├── test_spec.md                # TDD Specification with test cases\n│\n├── pkg/                        # Go packages (main source code)\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/  # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n│   ├── common/types/           # Shared type aliases (SandboxInfo, EntryPoint)\n│   ├── router/                 # HTTP router with JWT auth, proxy, session management\n│   ├── store/                  # Pluggable session store (Redis + Valkey)\n│   └── workloadmanager/        # K8s workload handler, reconciler, middleware\n│       ├── handler/\n│       ├── middleware/\n│       ├── reconciler/\n│       └── response/\n│\n├── client-go/                  # Generated Kubernetes client code\n│   ├── clientset/\n│   ├── informers/\n│   └── listers/\n│\n├── changes/                    # Change requests AR-001 through AR-015\n│   ├── AR-001/ through AR-015/  (each with proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, some with delta-spec.md)\n│\n├── code-execution/             # PicoD spec and design (derived from source)\n│   ├── spec.md                 # Full PicoD specification\n│   └── design.md               # Detailed design from reverse-engineered source\n│\n├── session-routing/            # Router spec and design\n├── session-store/              # Session store spec and design\n├── sandbox-orchestration/      # Sandbox orchestration spec and design\n├── ci-cd/                      # CI/CD design and spec\n├── deployment/                 # Deployment design, spec, client-go docs\n├── idle-cleanup/               # Idle cleanup spec and design\n├── integrations/               # Integration spec and design\n├── cli-toolkit/                # CLI toolkit spec and design\n├── python-sdk/                 # Python SDK spec and design\n├── testing/                    # TDD manifest\n│   └── agentcube_tdd_manifest.md\n```\n\n**Note:** There is NO `cmd/` directory, NO `docker/` directory, and NO `Makefile` yet. These are planned as part of AR-015 implementation. There is also NO `pkg/picod/` directory yet -- it is the target of AR-015.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `pkg/` Directory -- Existing Code and Picod References\n\nThe `pkg/` directory contains 5 subdirectories:\n\n| Package | Purpose | Key Files |\n|---------|---------|-----------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` | CRD type definitions | `shared_types.go`, `agent_type.go`, `codeinterpreter_types.go`, `constants.go`, `groupversion_info.go`, `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` |\n| `pkg/common/types/` | Type aliases | `types.go` (aliases `SandboxInfo` and `EntryPoint` from handler) |\n| `pkg/router/` | HTTP reverse proxy with session routing | `server.go`, `jwt.go`, `middleware.go`, `proxy.go`, `config.go`, `backend.go`, `session_manager.go`, etc. (16 files) |\n| `pkg/store/` | Pluggable session store | `store.go` (interface), `singleton.go`, `store_redis.go`, `store_valkey.go`, tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/` | K8s workload management | `handler/`, `middleware/`, `reconciler/`, `response/` subdirs |\n\n**Existing picod-related code:**\n\n1. **`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`** -- Defines `AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"` (line 13)\n2. **`pkg/router/jwt.go`** -- Defines `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"` (line 25) -- the K8s Secret storing RSA key pairs\n3. **`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go`** -- Also defines `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"` (line 53) and `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"` (line 54)\n4. **`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go`** -- Contains `injectPicodAuthEnv()` function (line 567) that reads the public key from the K8s Secret and injects it as `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable into sandbox containers\n\n**There is NO `pkg/picod/` directory yet.** AR-015 is the change request that will create it.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Specs, Docs, and Delta-Spec Files\n\n**Root-level spec/design files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` -- AR-014: Valkey store implementation (GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` -- AR-012: Session Store Interface\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` -- AR-011: Router JWT auth\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` -- Project context\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` -- TDD test case specification\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` -- Prompt for generating delta-spec.md for AR-015\n\n**Most critical for PicoD spec writing:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md` -- **Full PicoD specification** (179 lines, detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/design.md` -- **Detailed design from reverse-engineered source** (245 lines, exact Go struct definitions, route registration, middleware behavior, path sanitization algorithm)\n\n**AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API) change request:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md` -- **Comprehensive proposal** (178 lines) with package layout, request/response structures, route table, impact analysis, risk assessment, alternatives, and acceptance criteria\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/design.md` -- **Skeleton design** (74 lines, mostly TODOs)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md` -- **Skeleton tasks** (46 lines, mostly TODOs)\n\n**Delta-spec examples (format reference):**\n- `changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md` -- CRD shared types (good format example)\n- `changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md` (also at root as `delta-spec.md`) -- Valkey store (most recent, best format example)\n- `changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md` through `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md` -- Various earlier deltas\n\n**Per-feature spec/design pairs:**\n- `code-execution/spec.md` + `code-execution/design.md` -- PicoD\n- `session-routing/spec.md` + `session-routing/design.md` -- Router\n- `session-store/spec.md` + `session-store/design.md` -- Store\n- `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` + `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` -- Orchestration\n- `ci-cd/spec.md` + `ci-cd/design.md` -- CI/CD\n- `deployment/spec.md` + `deployment/design.md` -- Deployment\n- `idle-cleanup/spec.md` + `idle-cleanup/design.md` -- Idle cleanup\n- `integrations/spec.md` + `integrations/design.md` -- Integrations\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md` + `cli-toolkit/design.md` -- CLI\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` + `python-sdk/design.md` -- Python SDK\n\n---\n\n### 4. Go Module Structure\n\n```go\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\ngo 1.25.0\n```\n\n**Key direct dependencies:**\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP framework (used by Router, needed by PicoD) |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT RS256 (used by Router, needed by PicoD) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | UUID generation |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.22.0 | Metrics |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.18.0 | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.73 | Valkey client |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | Testing |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | K8s API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s apimachinery |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | K8s client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.22.2 | Controller runtime |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing API Definitions and Command Execution Patterns\n\n**HTTP Framework Pattern (Gin):**\n- All services use Gin with `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` and `gin.New()`\n- Global middleware: `gin.Logger()`, `gin.Recovery()`\n- Route groups with `.Group(\"/prefix\")` and `.Use(middleware)` pattern\n- Health endpoints are public (no auth); API endpoints are protected\n\n**Server Pattern (from `pkg/router/server.go`):**\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config  *Config\n    engine  *gin.Engine\n    // ... other fields\n}\n\nfunc NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error) { ... }\nfunc (s *Server) registerRoutes() { ... }\nfunc (s *Server) Start() error { ... }\nfunc (s *Server) Run() { ... }  // Signal handling + graceful shutdown\nfunc (s *Server) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error { ... }\n```\n\n**Auth Middleware Pattern (from `pkg/router/middleware.go`):**\n```go\nfunc AuthMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager) gin.HandlerFunc {\n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        // 1. Check Authorization header\n        // 2. Parse \"Bearer <token>\" format\n        // 3. Validate JWT via jwtManager.ParseAndValidateToken()\n        // 4. On failure: c.JSON(401, gin.H{\"error\": ..., \"code\": ...}); c.Abort()\n        // 5. On success: c.Set(\"claims\", claims); c.Next()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**JWT Verification Pattern (from `pkg/router/jwt.go`):**\n- RSA key generation: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n- Token signing: `jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, claims)`\n- Token parsing: `jwt.Parse(tokenString, keyFunc, jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute))`\n- Key function requires `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA` type assertion\n- K8s Secret persistence: `picod-router-identity` with `private.pem` and `public.pem`\n\n**Error Response Pattern:**\n```go\n// Generic errors (400/500):\nc.JSON(http.StatusBadRequest, gin.H{\"error\": \"message\", \"code\": 400})\n\n// Auth errors (401):\nc.JSON(http.StatusUnauthorized, gin.H{\"error\": \"message\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"details\"})\n```\n\n**Store Interface Pattern (from `pkg/store/store.go`):**\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    // ... more methods\n}\n\nfunc Storage() Store { ... }  // sync.Once singleton\n```\n\n**Constants Pattern (from `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go`):**\n- GVRs as `var` (schema.GroupVersionResource)\n- Kind strings as `const`\n- Label/Annotation keys as `const`\n- Identity/secret names as `const`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Picod/Pico/Command Execution References Summary\n\n| Location | Reference |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go:13` | `AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"` |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go:25` | `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go:53` | `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go:567` | `injectPicodAuthEnv()` function |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go:607` | Env var name `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` |\n| `code-execution/spec.md` | Full PicoD spec (command execution, file upload/list/download, health, JWT auth) |\n| `code-execution/design.md` | Detailed design with exact Go struct definitions, constants, route registration, path sanitization algorithm |\n| `changes/AR-015/proposal.md` | AR-015 proposal -- PicoD Command Execution API |\n| `changes/AR-015/design.md` | Skeleton design (TODOs) |\n| `changes/AR-015/tasks.md` | Skeleton tasks (TODOs) |\n| `.sdd_prompt.md` | Prompt to generate delta-spec.md for AR-015 |\n| `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | Test-PD-1 (OOM), Test-PD-2 (large stdout) |\n| `test_spec.md` | TestCase-PD-001 (Python execution), TestCase-PD-002 (error handling) |\n| `deployment/design.md` | Dockerfile.picod definition (golang:1.24.4 builder, ubuntu:24.04 runtime) |\n| `deployment/spec.md` | picod image build spec |\n| `ci-cd/design.md` | `docker-build-picod`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` Makefile targets |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` | CodeInterpreter with `AuthMode == picod` handling |\n| `session-routing/design.md` | Router JWT identity secret `picod-router-identity` |\n\n---\n\n### Key Insights for Writing the PicoD Delta Spec\n\n1. **The `code-execution/spec.md` and `code-execution/design.md` files are the most authoritative sources** for what PicoD should implement. They contain detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios and exact Go struct definitions derived from a reference implementation.\n\n2. **The AR-015 proposal.md is comprehensive** and defines the package layout (`config.go`, `server.go`, `auth.go`, `execute.go`, `files.go`, `types.go`), route table, request/response structures, and acceptance criteria.\n\n3. **The delta-spec.md format** follows a pattern of: `### Requirement: <name>` followed by `#### Scenario: <name>` with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN bullets. See `delta-spec.md` (AR-014) as the most recent example.\n\n4. **PicoD's planned package structure** is:\n   ```\n   pkg/picod/\n   ├── config.go       -- Config struct, CLI flag parsing\n   ├── server.go       -- Server struct, NewServer, Run, route registration\n   ├── auth.go         -- AuthManager, JWT middleware, key loading\n   ├── execute.go      -- ExecuteHandler, command execution logic\n   ├── files.go        -- Upload/List/Download handlers, path sanitization\n   └── types.go        -- Request/Response structs, constants\n   ```\n\n5. **Key constants to define:**\n   - `TimeoutExitCode = 124`\n   - `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n   - `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n   - `maxFileMode = 0777`\n   - Default timeout: 60 seconds\n   - Default port: 8080\n   - Default file mode: 0644\n   - Directory creation mode: 0755\n\n6. **Routes:**\n   - `GET /health` (no auth)\n   - `POST /api/execute` (JWT)\n   - `POST /api/files` (JWT) -- multipart or JSON Base64 upload\n   - `GET /api/files?path=` (JWT) -- directory listing\n   - `GET /api/files/*path` (JWT) -- file download\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_287c6a97cffexZpvg5hUCpcEXX","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775838516864,"end":1775838694251}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775838694308,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c0b6e0014gsy9N2h59KaGu","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7839314e0014Ovqxz33CXYbBB","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19686,"input":19235,"output":275,"reasoning":176,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.006053461}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775838695894,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c11d3001IJ7ovWhh8ncWNe","messageID":"msg_d783c0bbb001A6TAOfe8mKI9pW","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838701176,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c228d0016Ijzr4JwbRhBwF","messageID":"msg_d783c0bbb001A6TAOfe8mKI9pW","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_84d028cc0e424b8ba79717ab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Code Execution (PicoD) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Command execution API\n10: \n11: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/execute` with a JSON body, run `command[0]` with `command[1:]` as arguments via `exec.CommandContext`, capture stdout and stderr into buffers, and respond with HTTP 200 and an `ExecuteResponse` for successful request handling (including non-zero command exit). The request SHALL NOT accept stdin from the client; the process stdin is not set from the request body.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Valid execution with defaults\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body with non-empty `command` and empty `timeout`\n16: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n17: - **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` (seconds), `start_time`, and `end_time` as JSON\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Custom timeout\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body where `timeout` is a non-empty string parseable by Go `time.ParseDuration` (e.g. `\"30s\"`, `\"500ms\"`)\n22: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n23: - **THEN** the server uses that duration for the command context timeout\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Timeout exceeded\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** execution exceeds the context deadline\n28: - **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n29: - **THEN** the response `exit_code` SHALL be `124` (`TimeoutExitCode`) and stderr SHALL include a message that the command timed out with the timeout length in seconds (integer formatting)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Invalid timeout\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `timeout` is non-empty and not a valid duration\n34: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n35: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON `error` describing invalid timeout format and `code` 400\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Empty command\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** JSON binds successfully but `command` has length zero\n40: - **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n41: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"command cannot be empty\"` and `code` 400\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Working directory inside workspace\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `working_dir` is non-empty\n46: - **WHEN** the server resolves it with the same path-safety rules as file APIs\n47: - **THEN** `cmd.Dir` is set to the sanitized absolute path; if resolution fails, the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` prefixed by `\"Invalid working directory: \"`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Environment augmentation\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** `env` is non-empty\n52: - **WHEN** the command runs\n53: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` is the current process environment plus additional entries `key=value` for each map entry\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Malformed JSON\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** the body is not valid JSON for `ExecuteRequest`\n58: - **WHEN** binding fails\n59: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` from the binder and `code` 400\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: File upload API\n62: \n63: The system SHALL accept `POST /api/files`. If `Content-Type` starts with `multipart/form-data`, the server SHALL treat the request as multipart upload; otherwise it SHALL bind JSON for `UploadFileRequest`.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Multipart upload\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** `Content-Type` has prefix `multipart/form-data`, form field `path` is set, and form file `file` is present\n68: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n69: - **THEN** the server creates parent directories with mode `0755`, writes the uploaded stream to a sanitized path, applies mode from form field `mode` via `parseFileMode` (default `0644` when empty/invalid/exceeds max), and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` using `path` as relative to the workspace root\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Multipart missing path or file\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** multipart request with empty `path` or missing/unreadable `file`\n74: - **WHEN** the handler runs\n75: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with an appropriate `error` and `code` 400\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: JSON Base64 upload\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** non-multipart request with JSON `path` and `content` (Base64 standard encoding) required\n80: - **WHEN** the client posts to `POST /api/files`\n81: - **THEN** the server decodes content, creates directories, writes the file with `parseFileMode` on `mode`, and responds HTTP 200 with `FileInfo` (relative `path`)\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Invalid Base64\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** JSON upload with invalid Base64 in `content`\n86: - **WHEN** decoding fails\n87: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing invalid base64 and `code` 400\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: File listing API\n90: \n91: The system SHALL accept `GET /api/files?path=...`, require the `path` query parameter, read the directory at the sanitized path, and return JSON `ListFilesResponse`.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Successful listing\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `path` refers to an existing directory inside the workspace\n96: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files?path=<dir>`\n97: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `files` as an array of `FileEntry` objects (`name`, `size`, `modified`, `mode`, `is_dir`), skipping entries where `entry.Info()` fails\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Missing query parameter\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** the `path` query parameter is absent or empty\n102: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files`\n103: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"Missing 'path' query parameter\"` and `code` 400\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Directory not found\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** sanitized path does not exist\n108: - **WHEN** `os.ReadDir` fails with not exist\n109: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` `\"Directory not found\"` and `code` 404\n110: \n111: ### Requirement: File download API\n112: \n113: The system SHALL serve file contents at `GET /api/files/*path` for a sanitized file path, set download-oriented headers, and stream the file with `c.File`.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Successful download\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** the wildcard path resolves to a regular file inside the workspace\n118: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/<path>`\n119: - **THEN** the server sets `Content-Description` to `File Transfer`, `Content-Transfer-Encoding` to `binary`, `Content-Disposition` to `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`, `Content-Type` from `mime.TypeByExtension` or `application/octet-stream`, and returns the file body\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Path escapes workspace\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the requested path fails `sanitizePath`\n124: - **WHEN** the client calls the download endpoint\n125: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` describing access denied / workspace jail\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Not a file\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** the path exists but is a directory\n130: - **WHEN** the client downloads\n131: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` `\"Path is a directory, not a file\"` and `code` 400\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: File missing\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** the path does not exist\n136: - **WHEN** stat fails with not exist\n137: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `error` `\"File not found\"` and `code` 404\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Health endpoint\n140: \n141: The system SHALL expose `GET /health` without JWT middleware and respond HTTP 200 with JSON including `status`, `service`, `version`, and `uptime`.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Unauthenticated health\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** no `Authorization` header\n146: - **WHEN** the client calls `GET /health`\n147: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `status` `\"ok\"`, `service` `\"PicoD\"`, `version` `\"0.0.1\"`, and `uptime` as a string from `time.Since(server start)`\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: JWT authentication for API routes\n150: \n151: The system SHALL register `/api` routes under a Gin group that uses `AuthManager.AuthMiddleware`. The middleware SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`, parse the JWT with an RSA public key, and reject non-RSA signing methods. Valid tokens SHALL allow the request to proceed; after validation the request body SHALL be wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` limiting size to `MaxBodySize`.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Missing or malformed Authorization\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** missing header, or a header that is not exactly two space-separated parts with first part `Bearer`\n156: - **WHEN** an `/api` route is hit\n157: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with JSON including `error`, `code` 401, and `detail` explaining the failure\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Invalid or expired JWT\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** a Bearer token that fails verification (signature, expiry, etc.) with options `WithExpirationRequired`, `WithIssuedAt`, and `WithLeeway(1 minute)`\n162: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n163: - **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with `error` `\"Invalid token\"`, `code` 401, and `detail` containing the verification error\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Public key required at startup\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is unset or does not decode to an RSA public key in PEM form\n168: - **WHEN** `NewServer` initializes\n169: - **THEN** the process SHALL log a fatal error and not continue serving (there is no unauthenticated API mode when the key is missing)\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Server configuration\n172: \n173: The system SHALL read CLI flags `-port` and `-workspace`, build `picod.Config`, and listen on `\":<port>\"`. If `workspace` is empty, the workspace root SHALL be the current working directory (fatal if `os.Getwd` fails). The HTTP server SHALL use `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Defaults from CLI\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** `-port` and `-workspace` use program defaults\n178: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n179: - **THEN** `port` defaults to `8080`, `workspace` defaults to empty (resolved to CWD), and Gin runs in `ReleaseMode` with `Logger` and `Recovery` middleware globally\n\n(End of file - total 179 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Code Execution (PicoD) Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Command execution API\n\nThe system SHALL accept `POST /api/execute` with a JSON body, run `command[0]` with `command[1:]` as arguments via `exec.CommandContext`, capture stdout and stderr into buffers, and respond with HTTP 200 and an `ExecuteResponse` for successful request handling (including non-zero command exit). The request SHALL NOT accept stdin from the client; the process stdin is not set from the request body.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid execution with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body with non-empty `command` and empty `timeout`\n- **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n- **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` (seconds), `start_time`, and `end_time` as JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md","time":{"start":1775838701165,"end":1775838701174}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838702302,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c2732001oIytRoZuklVSlg","messageID":"msg_d783c0bbb001A6TAOfe8mKI9pW","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b4070bf5361d4fc294a02a50","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Code Execution (PicoD) — Design (from source)\n2: \n3: Derived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n4: \n5: ## Packages and entrypoint\n6: \n7: - **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n8: \n9: ## CLI flags and defaults\n10: \n11: | Flag        | Type   | Default | Usage string |\n12: |------------|--------|---------|--------------|\n13: | `-port`    | `int`  | `8080`  | `Port for the PicoD server to listen on` |\n14: | `-workspace` | `string` | `\"\"` | `Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)` |\n15: \n16: `klog.InitFlags(nil)` is called so standard klog flags are also registered.\n17: \n18: ## Environment variables\n19: \n20: | Name | Constant | Usage |\n21: |------|----------|--------|\n22: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | PEM-encoded PKIX public key (`PUBLIC KEY` block). Loaded in `NewServer` via `AuthManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`. If empty, invalid PEM, or not `*rsa.PublicKey`, `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` returns an error and `NewServer` calls `klog.Fatalf` — **no serve without a valid key**. |\n23: \n24: ## Server configuration struct\n25: \n26: ```go\n27: type Config struct {\n28: \tPort      int    `json:\"port\"`\n29: \tWorkspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n30: }\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ## Internal server fields (`Server`)\n34: \n35: - `engine *gin.Engine`\n36: - `config Config`\n37: - `authManager *AuthManager`\n38: - `startTime time.Time` — set to `time.Now()` in `NewServer`\n39: - `workspaceDir string` — absolute workspace root after `setWorkspace`\n40: \n41: ### Workspace resolution\n42: \n43: - If `config.Workspace != \"\"`: `setWorkspace(config.Workspace)` → `filepath.Abs` when possible, else fallback to provided string.\n44: - Else: `os.Getwd()` (fatal on error).\n45: \n46: ## Constants\n47: \n48: | Name | Value | File | Meaning |\n49: |------|-------|------|---------|\n50: | `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | `execute.go` | Exit code when context deadline exceeded |\n51: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` | `http.MaxBytesReader` cap applied after successful JWT check |\n52: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Env var for PEM public key |\n53: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | `parseFileMode` rejects modes `> 0777` (falls back to `0644`) |\n54: \n55: ### Default timeouts and modes\n56: \n57: - **Execute default timeout** (when `ExecuteRequest.Timeout == \"\"`): `60 * time.Second` (note: struct comment in source says `\"30s\"` but code uses 60s).\n58: - **Directory creation** (`MkdirAll`): `0755`\n59: - **Default file mode** (`parseFileMode` empty/invalid/too large): `0644` (octal parsed with `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)`)\n60: \n61: ## Request / response structs (exact JSON tags)\n62: \n63: ### Execute\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type ExecuteRequest struct {\n67: \tCommand    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n68: \tTimeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n69: \tWorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n70: \tEnv        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n71: }\n72: \n73: type ExecuteResponse struct {\n74: \tStdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n75: \tStderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n76: \tExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n77: \tDuration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n78: \tStartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n79: \tEndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n80: }\n81: ```\n82: \n83: - **Binding**: `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)` on `POST /api/execute`.\n84: - **Command**: `exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)`\n85: - **Stdout/Stderr**: `bytes.Buffer` assigned to `cmd.Stdout` and `cmd.Stderr`; no `cmd.Stdin` assignment.\n86: - **Exit code**: If `errors.Is(ctx.Err(), context.DeadlineExceeded)` → `TimeoutExitCode`; else if `cmd.ProcessState != nil` → `ExitCode()`; else `1` and append `err.Error()` to stderr (with newline if stderr non-empty).\n87: \n88: ### Files — upload response / JSON body\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: type FileInfo struct {\n92: \tPath     string    `json:\"path\"`\n93: \tSize     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n94: \tMode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n95: \tModified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n96: }\n97: \n98: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n99: \tPath    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n100: \tContent string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n101: \tMode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n102: }\n103: ```\n104: \n105: - **Multipart**: `Content-Type` prefix `multipart/form-data` → `handleMultipartUpload`.\n106:   - Form: `c.PostForm(\"path\")`, `c.FormFile(\"file\")`, optional `c.PostForm(\"mode\")`.\n107: - **JSON**: `c.ShouldBindJSON` → Base64 decode `req.Content` with `base64.StdEncoding`.\n108: \n109: ### Files — listing\n110: \n111: ```go\n112: type FileEntry struct {\n113: \tName     string    `json:\"name\"`\n114: \tSize     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n115: \tModified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n116: \tMode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n117: \tIsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n118: }\n119: \n120: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n121: \tFiles []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n122: }\n123: ```\n124: \n125: - **Query**: `path := c.Query(\"path\")` (required non-empty).\n126: \n127: ## HTTP error JSON shapes (Gin `gin.H`)\n128: \n129: - **Generic** (400/500): `{\"error\": string, \"code\": int}` (`code` is numeric HTTP status).\n130: - **Auth** (401): `{\"error\": string, \"code\": int, \"detail\": string}`.\n131: \n132: ## Gin setup and route registration\n133: \n134: Pattern from `NewServer`:\n135: \n136: 1. `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)`\n137: 2. `engine := gin.New()`\n138: 3. Global: `engine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())`\n139: 4. `authManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` — fatal on error\n140: 5. API group:\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n144: api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n145: {\n146: \tapi.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n147: \tapi.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n148: \tapi.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n149: \tapi.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n150: }\n151: engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n152: ```\n153: \n154: - **Download param**: `path := c.Param(\"path\")`; then `strings.TrimPrefix(path, \"/\")` before `sanitizePath`.\n155: \n156: ## Health response\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: c.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\n160: \t\"status\":  \"ok\",\n161: \t\"service\": \"PicoD\",\n162: \t\"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n163: \t\"uptime\":  time.Since(s.startTime).String(),\n164: })\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ## HTTP server\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: server := &http.Server{\n171: \tAddr:              fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", s.config.Port),\n172: \tHandler:           s.engine,\n173: \tReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n174: }\n175: return server.ListenAndServe()\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ## JWT middleware (`AuthManager`)\n179: \n180: ### Types\n181: \n182: ```go\n183: type AuthManager struct {\n184: \tpublicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n185: \tmutex     sync.RWMutex\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: ### Key loading (`LoadPublicKeyFromEnv`)\n190: \n191: 1. `keyData := os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)`\n192: 2. If empty → error: `environment variable %s is not set`\n193: 3. `pem.Decode([]byte(keyData))` — nil block → error `failed to decode PEM block`\n194: 4. `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)` — on success assert `*rsa.PublicKey`\n195: \n196: ### `AuthMiddleware` behavior\n197: \n198: 1. `authHeader := c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n199: 2. If empty → 401 JSON missing header / JWT required detail\n200: 3. `parts := strings.Split(authHeader, \" \")` — require `len(parts) == 2` and `parts[0] == \"Bearer\"` else 401 invalid format (`Use Bearer <token>`)\n201: 4. `tokenString := parts[1]`\n202: 5. `jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) { ... }, jwt.WithExpirationRequired(), jwt.WithIssuedAt(), jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute))`\n203:    - Key func: require `token.Method` is `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`; return `am.publicKey` (read lock)\n204: 6. If `err != nil || !token.Valid` → 401 `Invalid token` + detail with verification error\n205: 7. `c.Request.Body = http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)`\n206: 8. `c.Next()`\n207: \n208: **Note**: Any RSA signing method instance satisfies the type assert (e.g. RS256 in tests); HS256 is rejected.\n209: \n210: ## Path security (`sanitizePath`)\n211: \n212: Used by upload, list, download, and execute `working_dir`.\n213: \n214: 1. If `s.workspaceDir == \"\"` → error `workspace directory not initialized`\n215: 2. `resolvedWorkspace := filepath.EvalSymlinks(s.workspaceDir)`; on error fall back to `filepath.Abs` or `filepath.Clean`\n216: 3. `resolvedWorkspace = filepath.Clean(resolvedWorkspace)`\n217: 4. `cleanPath := filepath.Clean(p)`; if absolute, strip leading `os.PathSeparator` from path string\n218: 5. `fullPathCandidate := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleanPath))`\n219: 6. `relPath, relErr := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, fullPathCandidate)` — error → access denied\n220: 7. If `strings.HasPrefix(relPath, \"..\"+separator)` or `relPath == \"..\"` → access denied\n221: 8. `resolvedFinalPath, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPathCandidate)`:\n222:    - If success: re-check `filepath.Rel` against `resolvedWorkspace` for `..` escape; pass → return `resolvedFinalPath`\n223:    - If error (e.g. path does not exist): return `fullPathCandidate` (already verified as inside workspace)\n224: \n225: **Upload/list responses** use `filepath.Rel(s.workspaceDir, safePath)` for JSON `path` on uploaded files (not `resolvedWorkspace` symlink expansion — `safePath` is the sanitized target path).\n226: \n227: ## Multipart vs JSON detection\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: contentType := c.ContentType()\n231: if strings.HasPrefix(contentType, \"multipart/form-data\") {\n232: \ts.handleMultipartUpload(c)\n233: } else {\n234: \ts.handleJSONBase64Upload(c)\n235: }\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ## File download headers (exact strings)\n239: \n240: - `Content-Description`: `File Transfer`\n241: - `Content-Transfer-Encoding`: `binary`\n242: - `Content-Disposition`: `fmt.Sprintf(\"attachment; filename=\\\"%s\\\"\", filepath.Base(safePath))`\n243: - `Content-Type`: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(safePath))` or `\"application/octet-stream\"`\n244: \n245: This document is sufficient to reconstruct handlers, routes, structs, and security checks without reading the repo.\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Code Execution (PicoD) — Design (from source)\n\nDerived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n\n## Packages and entrypoint\n\n- **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n\n## CLI flags and defaults\n\n| Flag        | Type   | Default | Usage string |\n|------------|--------|---------|--------------|\n| `-port`    | `int`  | `8080`  | `Port for the PicoD server to listen on` |\n| `-workspace` | `string` | `\"\"` | `Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)` |\n\n`klog.InitFlags(nil)` is called so standard klog flags are also registered.\n\n## Environment variables\n\n| Name | Constant | Usage |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/design.md","time":{"start":1775838702293,"end":1775838702300}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838703355,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c2b4d0016jaDsKApR6O4uD","messageID":"msg_d783c0bbb001A6TAOfe8mKI9pW","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_136fa0a01dee4d7a8a7ef083","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/picod\n4: **Language:** Go\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## 目的\n8: \n9: PicoD 是运行在每个沙箱 Pod 内部的轻量级命令执行守护进程，负责接收 JWT 认证的 HTTP 请求，在可配置的工作空间沙箱（workspace jail）内执行命令、管理文件，并提供健康检查端点。本变更将创建 `pkg/picod` 包和 `cmd/picod` 入口，实现完整的 API 服务，是 AgentCube 代码执行能力的核心组件。\n10: \n11: ## 范围\n12: \n13: ### 包含\n14: 1. **包结构** — 创建 `pkg/picod/` 目录，包含 server、auth、execute、files 四个子模块\n15: 2. **入口程序** — `cmd/picod/main.go`，解析 CLI 标志、构建 Config、启动服务\n16: 3. **HTTP 路由** — Gin 框架注册 `/api/execute`、`/api/files`（上传/列表/下载）、`/health` 端点\n17: 4. **JWT 认证** — RSA 公钥验证中间件，保护所有 `/api` 路由，`/health` 无需认证\n18: 5. **命令执行** — `exec.CommandContext` 带超时控制，捕获 stdout/stderr，返回结构化响应\n19: 6. **文件管理** — multipart 上传、Base64 JSON 上传、目录列表、文件下载\n20: 7. **路径安全** — `sanitizePath` 防止目录穿越，确保所有文件操作限制在 workspace jail 内\n21: 8. **CLI 标志** — `-port`（默认 8080）、`-workspace`（默认 CWD）\n22: 9. **环境变量** — `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`（PEM 编码 RSA 公钥，启动时必填）\n23: \n24: ### 不包含\n25: - JWT 密钥对的生成和管理（由 Router 组件负责，通过 K8s Secret `picod-router-identity` 存储）\n26: - 公钥注入逻辑（由 WorkloadManager 的 `injectPicodAuthEnv` 负责）\n27: - Docker 镜像构建配置（Dockerfile 已在部署设计中定义）\n28: - Helm Chart 模板（属于部署变更）\n29: \n30: ## 架构概要\n31: \n32: ```\n33: cmd/picod/main.go\n34:   └── pkg/picod/\n35:         ├── config.go       — Config struct, CLI flag parsing\n36:         ├── server.go       — Server struct, NewServer, Run, route registration\n37:         ├── auth.go         — AuthManager, JWT middleware, key loading\n38:         ├── execute.go      — ExecuteHandler, command execution logic\n39:         ├── files.go        — Upload/List/Download handlers, path sanitization\n40:         └── types.go        — Request/Response structs, constants\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ### 请求/响应结构\n44: \n45: ```\n46: ExecuteRequest\n47: ├── command:    []string (required)\n48: ├── timeout:    string (optional, default: 60s)\n49: ├── working_dir: string (optional)\n50: └── env:        map[string]string (optional)\n51: \n52: ExecuteResponse\n53: ├── stdout:     string\n54: ├── stderr:     string\n55: ├── exit_code:  int\n56: ├── duration:   float64 (seconds)\n57: ├── start_time: time.Time\n58: └── end_time:   time.Time\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ### 路由表\n62: \n63: | Method | Path | Auth | Handler |\n64: |--------|------|------|---------|\n65: | GET | `/health` | 无 | HealthCheckHandler |\n66: | POST | `/api/execute` | JWT | ExecuteHandler |\n67: | POST | `/api/files` | JWT | UploadFileHandler |\n68: | GET | `/api/files?path=` | JWT | ListFilesHandler |\n69: | GET | `/api/files/*path` | JWT | DownloadFileHandler |\n70: \n71: ## 影响分析\n72: \n73: ### 直接影响\n74: | 组件 | 影响 | 说明 |\n75: |------|------|------|\n76: | `pkg/picod/` | 新增 | 核心服务实现（server、auth、execute、files） |\n77: | `cmd/picod/` | 新增 | 二进制入口 |\n78: | `go.mod` | 新增依赖 | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`、`github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`、`k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n79: | `Makefile` | 新增目标 | `docker-build-picod`、`docker-buildx-picod`、`docker-push-picod` |\n80: \n81: ### 上游依赖（本变更依赖的已完成组件）\n82: | 组件 | 依赖关系 |\n83: |------|----------|\n84: | Router JWT 密钥对 | RSA 私钥用于签发 token，公钥存储在 K8s Secret `picod-router-identity` |\n85: | WorkloadManager | 通过 `injectPicodAuthEnv` 将公钥注入为 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 环境变量 |\n86: | CodeInterpreter CRD | `AuthModePicoD` 模式触发 PicoD 相关配置注入 |\n87: \n88: ### 下游依赖（本变更完成后解锁）\n89: | 组件 | 依赖关系 |\n90: |------|----------|\n91: | Router | 将 `/api/execute` 请求转发到沙箱内的 PicoD 端点 |\n92: | Python SDK / CLI | 通过 Router 代理调用 PicoD API 执行代码 |\n93: | Sandbox 镜像 | 包含 PicoD 二进制作为 sidecar 或主进程 |\n94: \n95: ### 无影响的组件\n96: - `pkg/apis/` — CRD 类型定义独立\n97: - `client-go/` — 生成代码不依赖 PicoD 实现\n98: - Router 核心逻辑 — 仅通过 HTTP 与 PicoD 交互，接口已定义\n99: \n100: ### 风险评估\n101: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n102: |------|------|----------|\n103: | 目录穿越攻击 | 高 | `sanitizePath` 双重校验（相对路径检查 + symlink 解析后二次验证） |\n104: | 命令注入 | 高 | `exec.CommandContext` 不使用 shell，参数数组直接传递 |\n105: | 资源耗尽（大文件/长超时） | 中 | `MaxBodySize` 32MiB 限制、超时默认 60s 可配置 |\n106: | 公钥缺失启动 | 中 | `klog.Fatalf` 拒绝无密钥启动，无降级模式 |\n107: | JWT 过期/伪造 | 中 | RSA 签名验证 + 过期检查 + 1 分钟 leeway |\n108: \n109: ## 备选方案\n110: \n111: ### 方案 A：独立 Go 二进制 + Gin HTTP（已选）\n112: **优点**：轻量、启动快、依赖少；Gin 生态成熟；与 Router 技术栈一致；便于容器化部署。\n113: **缺点**：需要维护独立的二进制和镜像。\n114: \n115: ### 方案 B：嵌入到 Sandbox 主进程作为库\n116: **优点**：无额外进程开销。\n117: **缺点**：与沙箱主业务逻辑耦合；语言绑定限制（非 Go 沙箱无法使用）；故障隔离差（PicoD panic 影响主进程）。**否决**。\n118: \n119: ### 方案 C：使用 gRPC 替代 HTTP\n120: **优点**：强类型接口、双向流式支持。\n121: **缺点**：增加 Router 侧 gRPC 代理复杂度；文件上传/下载场景 HTTP 更自然；与现有 Router 反向代理架构不兼容。**否决**。\n122: \n123: ### 方案 D：复用 Kubernetes Exec API（`kubectl exec` 模式）\n124: **优点**：无需额外组件。\n125: **缺点**：需要 API Server 权限；延迟高；无法实现 workspace jail 隔离；认证模型复杂。**否决**。\n126: \n127: ## 实现要点\n128: \n129: 1. **路径安全** — `sanitizePath` 实现四层防护：`EvalSymlinks` → `Clean` → `Rel` 检查 `..` 前缀 → 解析后二次 `Rel` 验证\n130: 2. **超时处理** — 超时退出码固定为 `124`（与 shell `timeout` 命令一致），stderr 追加超时信息（秒数取整）\n131: 3. **文件模式解析** — `parseFileMode` 使用八进制解析，超过 `0777` 或无效时回退到 `0644`\n132: 4. **JWT 中间件** — 验证通过后注入 `http.MaxBytesReader` 限制请求体大小\n133: 5. **多部分检测** — `Content-Type` 前缀匹配 `multipart/form-data`，否则走 JSON Base64 上传\n134: 6. **下载头设置** — 设置 `Content-Disposition: attachment` 等下载导向头部\n135: \n136: ## 验收标准\n137: \n138: 1. **接口实现**\n139:    - [ ] `POST /api/execute` 支持 command、timeout、working_dir、env 参数\n140:    - [ ] `POST /api/files` 支持 multipart 和 JSON Base64 两种上传模式\n141:    - [ ] `GET /api/files?path=` 返回目录列表\n142:    - [ ] `GET /api/files/*path` 支持文件下载\n143:    - [ ] `GET /health` 无需认证，返回 status/service/version/uptime\n144: \n145: 2. **Spec 合规**\n146:    - [ ] 超时默认 60s，超时退出码 124，stderr 包含超时秒数\n147:    - [ ] 空 command 返回 400 `\"command cannot be empty\"`\n148:    - [ ] 无效 timeout 格式返回 400\n149:    - [ ] 缺失 path 查询参数返回 400 `\"Missing 'path' query parameter\"`\n150:    - [ ] 目录不存在返回 404 `\"Directory not found\"`\n151:    - [ ] 文件不存在返回 404 `\"File not found\"`\n152:    - [ ] 路径为目录时下载返回 400 `\"Path is a directory, not a file\"`\n153:    - [ ] 目录穿越返回 400 access denied 错误\n154: \n155: 3. **认证安全**\n156:    - [ ] 缺失 Authorization 头返回 401\n157:    - [ ] 非 Bearer 格式返回 401\n158:    - [ ] 无效/过期 JWT 返回 401 `\"Invalid token\"`\n159:    - [ ] 非 RSA 签名方法被拒绝\n160:    - [ ] `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 缺失时 Fatal 退出\n161:    - [ ] 请求体限制 32MiB\n162: \n163: 4. **测试覆盖**\n164:    - [ ] 命令执行单元测试（正常、超时、空 command、无效 timeout）\n165:    - [ ] 文件操作单元测试（上传、列表、下载、路径穿越）\n166:    - [ ] JWT 认证单元测试（有效 token、过期、错误签名、错误格式）\n167:    - [ ] 路径安全测试（symlink 穿越、`..` 穿越、绝对路径剥离）\n168: \n169: 5. **代码质量**\n170:    - [ ] `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` 无告警\n171:    - [ ] `go test ./pkg/picod/...` 全部通过\n172:    - [ ] `go mod tidy` 后无未使用依赖\n173: \n174: ## 状态\n175: \n176: - [ ] 提案审查\n177: - [ ] 实现\n178: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 178 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n**Module:** pkg/picod\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** M\n\n## 目的\n\nPicoD 是运行在每个沙箱 Pod 内部的轻量级命令执行守护进程，负责接收 JWT 认证的 HTTP 请求，在可配置的工作空间沙箱（workspace jail）内执行命令、管理文件，并提供健康检查端点。本变更将创建 `pkg/picod` 包和 `cmd/picod` 入口，实现完整的 API 服务，是 AgentCube 代码执行能力的核心组件。\n\n## 范围\n\n### 包含\n1. **包结构** — 创建 `pkg/picod/` 目录，包含 server、auth、execute、files 四个子模块\n2. **入口程序** — `cmd/picod/main.go`，解析 CLI 标志、构建 Config、启动服务\n3. **HTTP 路由** — Gin 框架注册 `/api/execute`、`/api/files`（上传/列表/下载）、`/health` 端点\n4. **JWT 认证** — RSA 公钥验证中间件，保护所有 `/api` 路由，`/health` 无需认证\n5. **命令执行** — `exec.CommandContext` 带超时控制，捕获 stdout/stderr，返回结构化响应\n6. **文件管理** — multipart 上传、Base64 JSON 上传、目录列表、文件下载\n7. **路径安全** — `sanitizePath` 防止目录穿越，确保所有文件操作限制在 workspace jail 内","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775838703347,"end":1775838703354}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838704341,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c2f9f001LgIVEY6Reslawx","messageID":"msg_d783c0bbb001A6TAOfe8mKI9pW","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a60eba1681a14fbf98cc5240","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `pkg/store`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** S\n8: - **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\n13: The Valkey implementation SHALL construct a `valkey.Client` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`. The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` to be non-empty (comma-separated list split into `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Successful initialization with address and password\n16: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`\n17: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n18: - **THEN** a `valkey.Client` is constructed with `InitAddress: []string{\"localhost:6379\"}` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n19: - **AND** no error is returned\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Comma-separated addresses\n22: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set to `\"host1:6379,host2:6379\"`\n23: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n24: - **THEN** `InitAddress` is `[]string{\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\"}`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Missing address fails\n27: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is empty or unset\n28: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n29: - **THEN** initialization returns an error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR` is required\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n32: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n33: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n34: - **THEN** initialization fails with an error stating password is required\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Password bypass when explicitly disabled\n37: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty, and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set to `\"false\"` (case-insensitive)\n38: - **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n39: - **THEN** a `valkey.Client` is constructed with empty password\n40: - **AND** no error is returned\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: Valkey connection options\n43: The system SHALL build `valkey.ClientOption` with `InitAddress` from splitting `VALKEY_ADDR` by comma and `Password` from `VALKEY_PASSWORD`. Optional flags `DisableCache` and `ForceSingleClient` SHALL be set when their respective environment variables parse as true via `strconv.ParseBool`.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Options construction with defaults\n46: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=\"valkey-host:6380\"` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD=\"pass123\"`\n47: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n48: - **THEN** the returned `ClientOption` has `InitAddress: []string{\"valkey-host:6380\"}` and `Password: \"pass123\"`\n49: - **AND** `DisableCache` and `ForceSingleClient` are `false`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: DisableCache enabled\n52: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n53: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n54: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is `true` on `ClientOption`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: ForceSingleClient enabled\n57: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n58: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n59: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is `true` on `ClientOption`\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Invalid bool value ignored\n62: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=invalid`\n63: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n64: - **THEN** `DisableCache` remains `false` (ParseBool error, flag not set)\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox multi-command execution\n67: The Valkey implementation SHALL execute `StoreSandbox` via `DoMulti` with three commands: `SETNX` on the session key with JSON value, `ZADD` on `session:expiry` with score = `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())`, and `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())`. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch returns an error.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Successful store multi\n70: - **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt` and session id `s1`\n71: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called on the Valkey store\n72: - **THEN** `DoMulti` executes `SETNX session:s1 <json>`, `ZADD session:expiry <expires_unix> s1`, `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` and returns nil\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: Multi error propagation\n75: - **GIVEN** the Valkey server is unreachable during `StoreSandbox`\n76: - **WHEN** `DoMulti` executes\n77: - **THEN** the method returns a non-nil error and no partial state is committed\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n80: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n81: - **WHEN** the method executes\n82: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n83: - **AND** no Valkey commands are issued\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n86: - **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo` has `ExpiresAt == time.Time{}`\n87: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n88: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating ExpiresAt is required\n89: - **AND** no Valkey commands are issued\n90: \n91: ### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSandbox XX semantics\n92: The Valkey implementation SHALL use `SET key value XX` for `UpdateSandbox`. If the key does not exist, the response will not be `\"OK\"` and the system SHALL return an error indicating the key does not exist.\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Update existing key\n95: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` exists\n96: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n97: - **THEN** the JSON value is overwritten, response is `\"OK\"`, and the method returns nil\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Update missing key\n100: - **GIVEN** session key `session:s1` does not exist\n101: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n102: - **THEN** the method returns an error containing `key not exists`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected on update\n105: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n106: - **WHEN** the method executes\n107: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID multi-command execution\n110: The Valkey implementation SHALL execute `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` via `DoMulti` with three commands: `DEL` on the session key, `ZREM` on `session:expiry`, and `ZREM` on `session:last_activity`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Full deletion\n113: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists with entries in both ZSETs\n114: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` succeeds\n115: - **THEN** `GET session:s1` returns not found and both ZSETs no longer contain member `s1`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent session\n118: - **GIVEN** session `ghost` does not exist\n119: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"ghost\")` is called\n120: - **THEN** `DoMulti` executes (DEL returns 0, ZREM returns 0) and no error is returned\n121: \n122: ### Requirement: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID\n123: The Valkey implementation SHALL retrieve a sandbox document using `B().Get().Key(key)`. If the key does not exist (`IsValkeyNil` returns true), the system SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Existing session retrieved\n126: - **GIVEN** a sandbox document exists at key `session:s1`\n127: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` is called\n128: - **THEN** the bytes are unmarshaled to `*types.SandboxInfo` and returned with nil error\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Missing session returns ErrNotFound\n131: - **GIVEN** no key exists at `session:missing`\n132: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"missing\")` is called\n133: - **THEN** `IsValkeyNil` is true and the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes query\n136: The Valkey implementation SHALL query `session:expiry` using `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, and `Limit(0, limit)`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: List with limit zero\n139: - **GIVEN** expired sessions exist in the index\n140: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` is called\n141: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: List with positive limit\n144: - **GIVEN** three sessions have expiry scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n145: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 2)` is called\n146: - **THEN** at most two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: List with negative limit\n149: - **GIVEN** expired sessions exist\n150: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n151: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes query\n154: The Valkey implementation SHALL query `session:last_activity` using `Zrangebyscore` with the same score range pattern as `ListExpiredSandboxes`. When `limit <= 0`, the method SHALL return `nil, nil`.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Inactive list with negative limit\n157: - **GIVEN** inactive sessions exist\n158: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, -1)` is called\n159: - **THEN** the method returns `nil, nil`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Inactive list with positive limit\n162: - **GIVEN** two sessions have last-activity scores ≤ `before.Unix()`\n163: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 5)` is called\n164: - **THEN** up to two `SandboxInfo` pointers are returned\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity precondition\n167: The Valkey implementation SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists via `B().Exists().Key(key)` (result must be 1). If the key is absent, the method SHALL return `ErrNotFound`. Then `ZADD` the session id to `session:last_activity` with the activity score.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Activity update with zero time\n170: - **GIVEN** session `s1` exists and `at` is `time.Time{}`\n171: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called\n172: - **THEN** `ZADD session:last_activity <now_unix> s1` is executed\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Activity update for missing session\n175: - **GIVEN** session `s1` does not exist\n176: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", now)` is called\n177: - **THEN** `Exists` returns 0 and the method returns `ErrNotFound`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n180: - **GIVEN** empty session ID `\"\"`\n181: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n182: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating session ID is empty\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Valkey MGET orphan tolerance\n185: The Valkey implementation SHALL handle empty string results from `Mget` commands when loading sandboxes by session IDs via `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`. Entries with empty string results SHALL be skipped without failing the batch.\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Valkey orphan ZSET member\n188: - **GIVEN** session id `ghost` is in `session:last_activity` but `session:ghost` does not exist\n189: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` loads the batch via `Mget`\n190: - **THEN** `ghost` is omitted from the result slice\n191: - **AND** no error is raised\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: All keys present in MGET\n194: - **GIVEN** session ids `[\"a\", \"b\"]` both have corresponding keys with valid JSON\n195: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, [\"a\", \"b\"])` is called\n196: - **THEN** `Mget` returns both values and both are unmarshaled into the result slice\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Mixed present and missing keys\n199: - **GIVEN** session id `a` has a key but `b` does not\n200: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, [\"a\", \"b\"])` is called\n201: - **THEN** `b`'s empty result is skipped and only `a`'s `SandboxInfo` is returned\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: Valkey Ping response validation\n204: The Valkey implementation SHALL issue `PING` via `B().Ping()` and validate the string response equals `PONG`.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Healthy Valkey\n207: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is running\n208: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n209: - **THEN** the response is `PONG` and nil error is returned\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Unreachable Valkey\n212: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is down\n213: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n214: - **THEN** an error is returned indicating connection failure\n215: \n216: ### Requirement: Valkey Close operation\n217: The Valkey implementation SHALL close the client connection via `vs.cli.Close()` and return nil.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Client closed successfully\n220: - **GIVEN** an active Valkey store\n221: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n222: - **THEN** `vs.cli.Close()` is invoked and nil is returned\n223: \n224: ### Requirement: Valkey fixed key patterns\n225: The Valkey implementation SHALL use the following fixed key patterns: `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`, `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`, `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`.\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Session key construction\n228: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n229: - **WHEN** the store constructs the key\n230: - **THEN** the key is `session:abc`\n231: \n232: ### Requirement: Valkey ZSET score semantics\n233: The system SHALL use Unix seconds as scores in sorted sets. Expiry index score = `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store. Last activity score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`, `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: Expiry score is sandbox ExpiresAt\n236: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to a specific time T\n237: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` adds to `session:expiry`\n238: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: Last activity score is current time on store\n241: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called at time T\n242: - **WHEN** the sandbox is added to `session:last_activity`\n243: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Last activity score uses provided time on update\n246: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with time T\n247: - **WHEN** the ZADD is executed on `session:last_activity`\n248: - **THEN** the score is `float64(T.Unix())`\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE for Valkey\n251: When `STORE_TYPE` is set case-insensitively to `\"valkey\"`, the system SHALL construct the Valkey implementation.\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Valkey selected\n254: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"`\n255: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n256: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation is constructed\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive valkey match\n259: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"VALKEY\"`\n260: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n261: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation is constructed\n262: \n263: ### Requirement: Valkey struct definition\n264: The Valkey implementation SHALL define a `valkeyStore` struct with fields: `cli valkey.Client`, `sessionPrefix string`, `expiryIndexKey string`, `lastActivityIndexKey string`.\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Struct field initialization\n267: - **GIVEN** a new `valkeyStore` is constructed\n268: - **WHEN** fields are inspected\n269: - **THEN** `sessionPrefix` is `\"session:\"`, `expiryIndexKey` is `\"session:expiry\"`, `lastActivityIndexKey` is `\"session:last_activity\"`\n\n(End of file - total 269 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/store`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `session-store/spec.md`, `session-store/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\nThe Valkey implementation SHALL construct a `valkey.Client` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`. The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` to be non-empty (comma-separated list split into `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful initialization with address and password\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set to `\"localhost:6379\"` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is set to `\"secret\"`\n- **WHEN** the Valkey store initializes\n- **THEN** a `valkey.Client` is constructed with `InitAddress: []string{\"localhost:6379\"}` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n- **AND** no error is returned\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775838704334,"end":1775838704340}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775838704433,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c21aa001PJxKoBEIuhT6wf","messageID":"msg_d783c0bbb001A6TAOfe8mKI9pW","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"text","text":"Let me read the key reference files to craft the spec.","time":{"start":1775838704431,"end":1775838704431}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775838704451,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c3331001LKKXJgmpzADQWf","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d783c0bbb001A6TAOfe8mKI9pW","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":24551,"input":24142,"output":298,"reasoning":111,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.007338451}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775838711064,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c4d15001bZAVKJ5DhPlqN3","messageID":"msg_d783c3361001n3GlZFwLmbJv1g","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838822912,"sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","part":{"id":"prt_d783c5a6c001z4l26WjMKiX1lt","messageID":"msg_d783c3361001n3GlZFwLmbJv1g","sessionID":"ses_287c6da83ffer4IOyyPiRWq14D","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_19abf32d8c9747a783f6eb4c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/picod`, `cmd/picod`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `code-execution/spec.md`, `code-execution/design.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Server configuration and startup\n\nThe system SHALL define a `Config` struct with `Port int` and `Workspace string` fields. The system SHALL parse CLI flags `-port` (default `8080`) and `-workspace` (default `\"\"`). If `workspace` is empty, the workspace root SHALL be resolved to the current working directory via `os.Getwd()`; failure to resolve CWD SHALL be fatal. The HTTP server SHALL use `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds. Gin SHALL run in `ReleaseMode` with `gin.Logger()` and `gin.Recovery()` as global middleware.\n\n#### Scenario: Defaults from CLI\n\n- **GIVEN** `-port` and `-workspace` flags use program defaults\n- **WHEN** the binary starts\n- **THEN** `Port` defaults to `8080`, `Workspace` is empty (resolved to CWD at runtime)\n- **AND** Gin runs in `ReleaseMode`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom port and workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** `-port=9090` and `-workspace=/tmp/picod-workspace`\n- **WHEN** `NewServer` is called with the parsed config\n- **THEN** `config.Port` is `9090` and `config.Workspace` is `/tmp/picod-workspace`\n- **AND** the server listens on `:9090`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty workspace resolves to CWD\n\n- **GIVEN** `-workspace` is not provided (empty string)\n- **WHEN** `NewServer` initializes\n- **THEN** `workspaceDir` is set to the absolute path of the current working directory\n\n#### Scenario: CWD resolution failure is fatal\n\n- **GIVEN** `os.Getwd()` returns an error and `config.Workspace` is empty\n- **WHEN** `NewServer` attempts to resolve the workspace\n- **THEN** the process calls `klog.Fatalf` and does not start serving\n\n#### Scenario: Non-empty workspace is made absolute\n\n- **GIVEN** `config.Workspace` is set to a relative path like `./data`\n- **WHEN** `setWorkspace` runs\n- **THEN** `workspaceDir` is resolved to an absolute path via `filepath.Abs`\n\n### Requirement: Route registration\n\nThe system SHALL register routes on a `*gin.Engine` as follows: `GET /health` (no auth), and an `/api` group with `AuthManager.AuthMiddleware` containing `POST /execute`, `POST /files`, `GET /files` (query-based listing), and `GET /files/*path` (wildcard download).\n\n#### Scenario: Health endpoint is public\n\n- **GIVEN** a running PicoD server\n- **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` without any `Authorization` header\n- **THEN** the request is served without authentication\n\n#### Scenario: API routes require auth middleware\n\n- **GIVEN** a running PicoD server\n- **WHEN** a client calls `POST /api/execute` without a valid JWT\n- **THEN** the `AuthManager.AuthMiddleware` intercepts and returns HTTP 401\n\n#### Scenario: All five routes are registered\n\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the route table is inspected\n- **THEN** the following routes exist: `GET /health`, `POST /api/execute`, `POST /api/files`, `GET /api/files`, `GET /api/files/*path`\n\n### Requirement: Health check response\n\nThe system SHALL respond to `GET /health` with HTTP 200 and JSON containing `status: \"ok\"`, `service: \"PicoD\"`, `version: \"0.0.1\"`, and `uptime` as a string from `time.Since(serverStartTime)`.\n\n#### Scenario: Unauthenticated health response\n\n- **GIVEN** no `Authorization` header\n- **WHEN** the client calls `GET /health`\n- **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with JSON `{\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"PicoD\", \"version\": \"0.0.1\", \"uptime\": \"<duration>\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Uptime increases over time\n\n- **GIVEN** the server has been running for at least 1 second\n- **WHEN** `GET /health` is called\n- **THEN** the `uptime` field is a non-zero duration string (e.g. `\"1.234s\"`)\n\n### Requirement: JWT authentication middleware\n\nThe system SHALL define an `AuthManager` struct with a `*rsa.PublicKey` field protected by `sync.RWMutex`. The middleware SHALL require the `Authorization` header in `Bearer <token>` format, parse the JWT with RSA public key verification using `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`, and `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`. Non-RSA signing methods SHALL be rejected. On success, the request body SHALL be wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` limiting size to `MaxBodySize` (32 MiB).\n\n#### Scenario: Missing Authorization header\n\n- **GIVEN** no `Authorization` header is present\n- **WHEN** an `/api` route is hit\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with JSON `{\"error\": \"...\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"...\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Malformed Authorization header\n\n- **GIVEN** `Authorization` header is not two space-separated parts or does not start with `Bearer`\n- **WHEN** the middleware runs\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with JSON error indicating invalid format\n\n#### Scenario: Valid RSA JWT passes\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT signed with the corresponding RSA private key, not expired, with `iat` claim\n- **WHEN** the middleware runs\n- **THEN** `c.Request.Body` is wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader(..., MaxBodySize)` and `c.Next()` is called\n\n#### Scenario: Expired JWT is rejected\n\n- **GIVEN** a JWT whose `exp` claim is in the past (beyond 1 minute leeway)\n- **WHEN** the middleware runs\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 401 with `error: \"Invalid token\"` and `detail` containing the verification error\n\n#### Scenario: Non-RSA signing method rejected\n\n- **GIVEN** a JWT signed with HS256 (HMAC)\n- **WHEN** the key function asserts `token.Method` is `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n- **THEN** the type assertion fails and the middleware returns HTTP 401\n\n### Requirement: Public key loading from environment\n\nThe system SHALL load the RSA public key from the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable. The value SHALL be PEM-decoded and parsed via `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey`, asserting the result is `*rsa.PublicKey`. If the env var is unset, PEM decoding fails, or the key is not RSA, `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` SHALL return an error and `NewServer` SHALL call `klog.Fatalf`.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid PEM public key loaded\n\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` contains a valid PEM block with `PUBLIC KEY` type encoding an RSA public key\n- **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` is called\n- **THEN** `authManager.publicKey` is set to the parsed `*rsa.PublicKey` and no error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Missing environment variable\n\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is unset or empty\n- **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` is called\n- **THEN** an error is returned indicating the environment variable is not set\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid PEM block\n\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` contains text that is not valid PEM\n- **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` is called\n- **THEN** `pem.Decode` returns nil and an error `failed to decode PEM block` is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Non-RSA key rejected\n\n- **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` contains a valid PEM block encoding an ECDSA public key\n- **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` is called\n- **THEN** the type assertion to `*rsa.PublicKey` fails and an error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Server refuses to start without key\n\n- **GIVEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` returns an error\n- **WHEN** `NewServer` initializes\n- **THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is called and the process exits\n\n### Requirement: Command execution handler\n\nThe system SHALL accept `POST /api/execute` with JSON body binding to `ExecuteRequest`. The handler SHALL run `command[0]` with `command[1:]` as arguments via `exec.CommandContext`, capture stdout and stderr into `bytes.Buffer`, and respond with HTTP 200 and `ExecuteResponse` JSON. The request SHALL NOT accept stdin from the client.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid execution with default timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid JWT and JSON body `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"]}` with empty `timeout`\n- **WHEN** the client calls `POST /api/execute`\n- **THEN** the server uses a default timeout of 60 seconds, runs the command, and returns `{\"stdout\": \"hello\\n\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"exit_code\": 0, \"duration\": <float>, \"start_time\": <time>, \"end_time\": <time>}`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** JSON body with `\"timeout\": \"500ms\"`\n- **WHEN** the handler runs\n- **THEN** the command context timeout is set to 500 milliseconds\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout exceeded\n\n- **GIVEN** a command that runs longer than the specified timeout (e.g. `sleep 10` with `\"timeout\": \"1s\"`)\n- **WHEN** the context deadline is exceeded\n- **THEN** `exit_code` is `124` (`TimeoutExitCode`) and `stderr` includes a message that the command timed out with the timeout length formatted as an integer number of seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid timeout format\n\n- **GIVEN** `\"timeout\": \"not-a-duration\"`\n- **WHEN** the handler attempts to parse the timeout\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON `{\"error\": \"invalid timeout format: ...\", \"code\": 400}`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty command array\n\n- **GIVEN** JSON body `{\"command\": []}`\n- **WHEN** the handler validates the request\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `{\"error\": \"command cannot be empty\", \"code\": 400}`\n\n#### Scenario: Malformed JSON body\n\n- **GIVEN** the request body is not valid JSON\n- **WHEN** `ShouldBindJSON` is called\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with the binder error and `code: 400`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-zero exit code is captured\n\n- **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 1 (e.g. `[\"sh\", \"-c\", \"exit 1\"]`)\n- **WHEN** the command completes\n- **THEN** the response `exit_code` is `1` and the response is HTTP 200\n\n#### Scenario: Working directory inside workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** `\"working_dir\": \"subdir\"` and the workspace contains `subdir/`\n- **WHEN** the handler resolves the working directory\n- **THEN** `cmd.Dir` is set to the sanitized absolute path of `workspaceDir/subdir`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid working directory\n\n- **GIVEN** `\"working_dir\": \"../../etc\"` that would escape the workspace\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` prefixed by `\"Invalid working directory: \"`\n\n#### Scenario: Environment augmentation\n\n- **GIVEN** `\"env\": {\"FOO\": \"bar\", \"BAZ\": \"qux\"}`\n- **WHEN** the command runs\n- **THEN** `cmd.Env` includes `FOO=bar` and `BAZ=qux` in addition to the current process environment\n\n### Requirement: File upload handler (multipart)\n\nThe system SHALL detect `Content-Type` with prefix `multipart/form-data` and handle as multipart upload. The handler SHALL read form field `path`, form file `file`, and optional form field `mode`. Parent directories SHALL be created with mode `0755`. The file SHALL be written to a sanitized path with mode from `parseFileMode` (default `0644`).\n\n#### Scenario: Successful multipart upload\n\n- **GIVEN** multipart request with `path=\"test/hello.txt\"`, file content `\"world\"`, and `mode=\"0644\"`\n- **WHEN** the handler runs\n- **THEN** parent directory `test/` is created with mode `0755`, the file is written with mode `0644`, and HTTP 200 returns `{\"path\": \"test/hello.txt\", \"size\": 5, \"mode\": \"-rw-r--r--\", \"modified\": \"<time>\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart missing path\n\n- **GIVEN** multipart request with no `path` form field\n- **WHEN** the handler runs\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON error indicating missing path\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart missing file\n\n- **GIVEN** multipart request with `path` set but no `file` form field\n- **WHEN** the handler runs\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON error indicating missing file\n\n#### Scenario: File mode exceeds max\n\n- **GIVEN** multipart upload with `mode=\"07777\"` (exceeds `maxFileMode` of `0777`)\n- **WHEN** `parseFileMode` is called\n- **THEN** the mode falls back to `0644`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid file mode falls back\n\n- **GIVEN** multipart upload with `mode=\"abc\"`\n- **WHEN** `parseFileMode` is called\n- **THEN** the mode falls back to `0644`\n\n### Requirement: File upload handler (JSON Base64)\n\nThe system SHALL bind non-multipart requests to `UploadFileRequest` with required `path` and `content` (Base64 standard encoding). The handler SHALL decode `content` via `base64.StdEncoding`, create parent directories with mode `0755`, write the file with `parseFileMode` on `mode`, and respond with `FileInfo`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful Base64 upload\n\n- **GIVEN** JSON body `{\"path\": \"data.bin\", \"content\": \"<base64-encoded-bytes>\", \"mode\": \"0755\"}`\n- **WHEN** the handler runs\n- **THEN** the decoded bytes are written to `workspaceDir/data.bin` with mode `0755` and HTTP 200 returns `FileInfo`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid Base64 content\n\n- **GIVEN** JSON body with `\"content\": \"not-valid-base64!!!\"`\n- **WHEN** `base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString` is called\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON error describing invalid base64\n\n#### Scenario: Empty mode defaults to 0644\n\n- **GIVEN** JSON body with `\"mode\": \"\"`\n- **WHEN** `parseFileMode` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `os.FileMode` is `0644`\n\n### Requirement: File listing handler\n\nThe system SHALL accept `GET /api/files?path=...`, require the `path` query parameter to be non-empty, read the directory at the sanitized path via `os.ReadDir`, and return `ListFilesResponse` with an array of `FileEntry` objects. Entries where `entry.Info()` fails SHALL be skipped.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful directory listing\n\n- **GIVEN** `path=\"\"` (empty string, meaning workspace root) and the workspace contains files\n- **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files?path=`\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 200 with `{\"files\": [{\"name\": \"...\", \"size\": N, \"modified\": \"...\", \"mode\": \"...\", \"is_dir\": bool}]}`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing path query parameter\n\n- **GIVEN** no `path` query parameter or `path` is empty\n- **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files`\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `{\"error\": \"Missing 'path' query parameter\", \"code\": 400}`\n\n#### Scenario: Directory not found\n\n- **GIVEN** `path=\"nonexistent\"` and the directory does not exist\n- **WHEN** `os.ReadDir` is called\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"Directory not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n\n#### Scenario: Subdirectory listing\n\n- **GIVEN** `path=\"subdir\"` and `subdir/` exists inside the workspace\n- **WHEN** the handler runs\n- **THEN** entries within `subdir/` are returned as `FileEntry` objects\n\n#### Scenario: Entries with stat errors are skipped\n\n- **GIVEN** a directory containing an entry where `entry.Info()` returns an error\n- **WHEN** the handler iterates entries\n- **THEN** the problematic entry is omitted from the response and no error is returned\n\n### Requirement: File download handler\n\nThe system SHALL serve file contents at `GET /api/files/*path`. The wildcard path parameter SHALL be trimmed of its leading `/` before sanitization. The handler SHALL set download-oriented headers (`Content-Description: File Transfer`, `Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary`, `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`, `Content-Type` from `mime.TypeByExtension` or `application/octet-stream`) and stream the file via `c.File`.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful file download\n\n- **GIVEN** a regular file exists at `workspaceDir/docs/readme.md`\n- **WHEN** the client calls `GET /api/files/docs/readme.md`\n- **THEN** the response includes `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=\"readme.md\"`, appropriate `Content-Type`, and the file body\n\n#### Scenario: Path escapes workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** `GET /api/files/../../etc/passwd`\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with JSON error describing access denied / workspace jail violation\n\n#### Scenario: Path is a directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the wildcard path resolves to a directory inside the workspace\n- **WHEN** the handler checks the file type\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 400 with `{\"error\": \"Path is a directory, not a file\", \"code\": 400}`\n\n#### Scenario: File not found\n\n- **GIVEN** the path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `os.Stat` fails with `os.IsNotExist`\n- **THEN** the server responds HTTP 404 with `{\"error\": \"File not found\", \"code\": 404}`\n\n#### Scenario: Unknown extension defaults to octet-stream\n\n- **GIVEN** a file with no recognized extension (e.g. `data.blob`)\n- **WHEN** `mime.TypeByExtension` is called\n- **THEN** `Content-Type` is set to `application/octet-stream`\n\n### Requirement: Path sanitization (sanitizePath)\n\nThe system SHALL implement `sanitizePath` with the following algorithm: (1) if `workspaceDir` is empty, return error `workspace directory not initialized`; (2) resolve `workspaceDir` via `filepath.EvalSymlinks`, falling back to `filepath.Abs` or `filepath.Clean` on error; (3) clean the resolved workspace; (4) clean the input path, stripping leading `os.PathSeparator` if absolute; (5) join with resolved workspace and clean; (6) verify via `filepath.Rel` that the result does not start with `..` or equal `..`; (7) attempt `filepath.EvalSymlinks` on the candidate — if successful, re-verify with `filepath.Rel`; if `EvalSymlinks` fails (path does not exist), return the already-verified candidate path.\n\n#### Scenario: Simple relative path\n\n- **GIVEN** `workspaceDir=\"/workspace\"` and input path `\"subdir/file.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n- **THEN** the result is `/workspace/subdir/file.txt` with no error\n\n#### Scenario: Directory traversal blocked\n\n- **GIVEN** input path `\"../../etc/passwd\"`\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n- **THEN** an error is returned indicating access denied / workspace jail violation\n\n#### Scenario: Absolute path is stripped\n\n- **GIVEN** input path `\"/etc/passwd\"`\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n- **THEN** the leading `/` is stripped and the path is treated as `etc/passwd` relative to workspace\n\n#### Scenario: Symlink inside workspace allowed\n\n- **GIVEN** a symlink inside the workspace pointing to another location inside the workspace\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` resolves the path\n- **THEN** `EvalSymlinks` succeeds and the resolved path is re-verified to be inside the workspace\n\n#### Scenario: Symlink escape blocked\n\n- **GIVEN** a symlink inside the workspace pointing to a location outside the workspace\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` resolves the path\n- **THEN** the re-verification via `filepath.Rel` detects the `..` prefix and returns an access denied error\n\n#### Scenario: Non-existent path inside workspace allowed\n\n- **GIVEN** input path `\"new-file.txt\"` that does not yet exist but is inside the workspace\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n- **THEN** `EvalSymlinks` fails (path does not exist), but the already-verified candidate path is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Empty workspace directory\n\n- **GIVEN** `workspaceDir` is empty string\n- **WHEN** `sanitizePath` is called\n- **THEN** an error `workspace directory not initialized` is returned\n\n### Request/Response type definitions\n\nThe system SHALL define the following structs with exact JSON tags:\n\n```go\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n    Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n    WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n    Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n}\n\ntype ExecuteResponse struct {\n    Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n    Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n    ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n    Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n    StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n    EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n}\n\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n}\n\ntype UploadFileRequest struct {\n    Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n}\n\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n}\n\ntype ListFilesResponse struct {\n    Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Scenario: ExecuteRequest binding\n\n- **GIVEN** JSON body `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\", \"working_dir\": \"src\", \"env\": {\"GOOS\": \"linux\"}}`\n- **WHEN** `ShouldBindJSON` is called\n- **THEN** all fields are populated correctly with their respective types\n\n#### Scenario: ExecuteResponse serialization\n\n- **GIVEN** a completed command execution\n- **WHEN** the response is serialized to JSON\n- **THEN** all six fields (`stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration`, `start_time`, `end_time`) are present with correct types\n\n### Requirement: Constants\n\nThe system SHALL define the following constants:\n\n| Name | Value | Meaning |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | Exit code when context deadline exceeded |\n| `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `http.MaxBytesReader` cap after JWT check |\n| `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | Env var for PEM public key |\n| `maxFileMode` | `0777` | Maximum allowed file mode in `parseFileMode` |\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout exit code value\n\n- **GIVEN** a command times out\n- **WHEN** the exit code is set\n- **THEN** it equals `124`\n\n#### Scenario: Max body size value\n\n- **GIVEN** `MaxBodySize` is referenced\n- **WHEN** its value is inspected\n- **THEN** it equals `33554432` (32 MiB)\n\n### Requirement: Server struct and lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL define a `Server` struct with fields: `engine *gin.Engine`, `config Config`, `authManager *AuthManager`, `startTime time.Time`, `workspaceDir string`. `NewServer` SHALL set `startTime = time.Now()`, initialize the auth manager, load the public key, resolve the workspace, register routes, and construct the `http.Server`. `Run` SHALL call `http.Server.ListenAndServe()`.\n\n#### Scenario: NewServer initializes all fields\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `Config` and `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` set\n- **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` is called\n- **THEN** all five struct fields are non-zero/non-nil: `engine`, `config`, `authManager`, `startTime`, `workspaceDir`\n\n#### Scenario: startTime is set at construction\n\n- **GIVEN** `NewServer` is called at time T\n- **WHEN** `server.startTime` is inspected\n- **THEN** it equals approximately T (within test tolerance)\n\n#### Scenario: Run starts listening\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid `Server` with `config.Port = 8080`\n- **WHEN** `server.Run()` is called\n- **THEN** the HTTP server begins listening on `:8080`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go\">\nERROR [78:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [83:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [88:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func(